# Cloudflare Pages headers for the docs site.
#
# Spec files served from this domain need permissive CORS so
# external tools (Postman, openapi-typescript, code-generation
# CLIs running in CI) can fetch them from arbitrary origins
# without preflight failures.
#
# The HTML index uses Scalar which does its own first-party fetch
# (same origin), so the catch-all CORS rule on /* is broad enough
# to cover everything the docs site serves without a per-extension
# carve-out.

/*
  Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *
  Access-Control-Allow-Methods: GET, HEAD, OPTIONS
  Access-Control-Allow-Headers: Content-Type
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff

# YAML files specifically — declare the right Content-Type so
# spec parsers don't fall back to the CF default (text/plain) and
# refuse to parse.
/*.yaml
  Content-Type: application/yaml; charset=utf-8

/*.yml
  Content-Type: application/yaml; charset=utf-8
